sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Dev as Developer
    participant ADO as Azure DevOps
    participant VS as VS Code
    participant Git as Local Git Repo
    participant Test as Local Test Runner

    Dev->>ADO: Create branch in Azure DevOps\nfeature/your-task
    Dev->>VS: Clone or open repo in VS Code\ngit clone <repo-url>\ncd repo\ncode .
    Dev->>Git: git fetch origin
    Dev->>Git: Switch to working branch\ngit checkout feature/your-task\nor\ngit checkout -b feature/your-task --track origin/feature/your-task

    loop Development cycle
        Dev->>VS: Develop in VS Code
        Dev->>Git: git status
        Dev->>Test: npm test
        Dev->>Git: git add .
        Dev->>Git: git commit -m "Your message"
        Dev->>Git: git push origin feature/your-task
        Git->>ADO: Update remote feature branch

        alt Main has changed
            Dev->>Git: git fetch origin
            Dev->>Git: git checkout feature/your-task
            Dev->>Git: git rebase origin/main

            alt Conflicts occur
                Dev->>VS: Resolve conflicts
                Dev->>Git: git add .
                Dev->>Git: git rebase --continue
            else No conflicts
                Note over Dev,Git: Rebase completes cleanly
            end

            Dev->>Test: npm test
            Dev->>Git: git push --force-with-lease origin feature/your-task
            Git->>ADO: Update rebased feature branch
        else Main has not changed
            Note over Dev,ADO: No rebase needed
        end

        alt Not ready for Pull Request
            Note over Dev,VS: Continue development on same branch
        else Ready for Pull Request
            Dev->>ADO: Create Pull Request
            ADO->>ADO: Run approval checks and validation

            alt PR not approved or checks fail
                Dev->>VS: Address feedback
                Dev->>Git: git add .
                Dev->>Git: git commit -m "Address feedback"
                Dev->>Git: git push origin feature/your-task
                Git->>ADO: Update PR branch
            else PR approved and checks passed
                Dev->>ADO: Merge PR into main
                Dev->>Git: git checkout main
                Dev->>Git: git pull origin main
                Dev->>Git: git checkout -b feature/next-task
                Note over Dev,Git: Start next task branch
            end
        end
    end